post_text:
Attention Parents/Guardians of Central Local Schools

School officials are getting calls about some misinformation that has appeared on various social media outlets. There is a false report that students who are exhibiting COVID-19-like symptoms will be moved to an undisclosed location without parent/guardian consent. Rest assured that this information is completely false.

The truth is that school officials will contact parents and work diligently with parents when it comes to students exhibiting COVID-19-like symptoms. The overall health and wellbeing of all students and staff members will be the top priority again this school year.

Parents/guardians with questions should contact either Mr. Arnold or a principal.

post_text: Attention parents of Fairview students: Please take a few minutes to complete the "School Reopening Survey for Parents" to provide school officials with input. The survey is available through Final Forms and will be live through 8:00 am on Wednesday, July 15. If you have questions about the content, contact Mr. Arnold at 419-658-2808. If you have any technical difficulties completing the survey, please see the Final Forms post on the front page of the school website. Under the header Latest News, you will find information about contacting the school for support. More information about how school will look this fall will be coming shortly. Thank you for your assistance.

Central Local Schools would like to thank our community for its support of the permanent improvement levy on November 5. With these additional resources, we will get to work making necessary repairs and upgrades to our facilities, bus fleet, and teaching materials.

Educating children is and always will be a group-effort, and our awesome community plays a vital role in the process. Again, we thank you very much.

Fairview Pride -- Community Wide
